The paper deals with the task of semantic parsing, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) that involves mapping natural language utterances to machine interpretable meaning representations. This task is closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), databases (cs.DB), and software engineering (cs.SE). Given that the paper proposes a novel approach to weakly-supervised semantic parsing that involves modeling structured alignments as latent variables, it is likely to be of interest to researchers in these sub-fields.
